PART 2: ADDITIONAL RESTRICTIONS (NO AI/ML TRAINING)
================================================================================

NOTWITHSTANDING any other provision of the AGPL-3.0 or any other
license that may apply, no part of this software, its source code,
documentation, configuration files, sample data, test fixtures, or
any derivative work thereof may be used, in whole or in part, to:

  (a) Train, fine-tune, validate, benchmark, or otherwise improve
      any artificial intelligence, machine learning, deep learning,
      neural network, or large language model system, whether for
      commercial, research, academic, government, or any other
      purpose. This includes but is not limited to:
        - Large language models (LLMs) such as GPT, Claude, LLaMA,
          Mistral, Qwen, DeepSeek, and their derivatives;
        - Code-generation models and AI pair-programming systems;
        - Image, audio, or video generation models;
        - Embedding models and vector search systems whose training
          data incorporates this software or its outputs;
        - Any system whose model weights, prompts, or fine-tuning
          data are derived from this software.

  (b) Create, contribute to, augment, or distribute any dataset
      intended for the training, fine-tuning, validation, or
      benchmarking of systems described in (a).

  (c) Use the outputs of this software (including any data,
      metadata, search results, bibliographic records, or text
      produced by this software) to train or improve any system
      described in (a), regardless of whether the outputs were
      obtained directly or through a derivative work.

  (d) Circumvent this restriction by using this software to produce
      intermediate representations, embeddings, or features that
      are subsequently used in any manner described in (a).

The restrictions in this PART 2 are irrevocable for the duration of
the copyright in this work and apply regardless of the licensing
status, organizational affiliation, or commercial nature of the
recipient's other activities.

Use of this software for any of the foregoing purposes without the
express prior written consent of the copyright holder is a material
breach of this license and shall, at the copyright holder's option,
terminate the licensee's rights under both PART 1 (AGPL-3.0) and
PART 2 (this No-AI-Training restriction).

EXCEPTIONS: The restrictions in this PART 2 do NOT apply to:
  - Use of this software for evaluation, security review, or
    interoperability testing, provided no model weights, training
    data, or derived AI/ML artifacts are produced or distributed;
  - Reading, running, and interacting with the software for
    personal, academic, or commercial productivity use;
  - Distribution of unmodified copies of this software's source
    code in accordance with AGPL-3.0.

